<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="tense-adj">tense <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tens/    美 /tens/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>(身体部位) 绷紧的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a face tense with anxiety
焦虑紧张的面孔</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(神经) 紧张的；担心的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When exposed to noise and strong light, I feel tense and restless.
一听到噪音或见到强光我就紧张不安。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(形势、事件) 令人紧张的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a tense political situation
紧张的政治局势</p></div></div>